# Kanban / bored card workflow

When this project (or you) uses **Kanban cards** (e.g. bored) as the task queue:

1. **One card at a time** unless the user explicitly says otherwise (no parallel cards unless told).

2. **Start work:** As soon as you pick up a card, **move it to the In Progress column** using **bored MCP** (`list_columns` ‚Üí **`move_card`**). Resolve the card with **`get_card_by_number`** when you only know `#N`.

3. **Reconcile with reality:** **Compare the card body to the current source tree**, **replan** if scope or facts drifted, then **`update_card`** so the card stays accurate (acceptance, files, out-of-scope notes).

4. **Branches:** Implement each card on its **own feature branch** whose name includes the **next consecutive iteration number** for that repo (e.g. `feat/iteration-22-short-slug`).  
   **Never** create follow-on branches **from** the feature branch ‚Äî always branch from **`main`** (or the repo‚Äôs agreed default trunk), one iteration branch per card.

5. **Ship:** When the **PR is merged**, **move the card to Done** via bored MCP (**`move_card`** into the Done column).

## Bored ‚Äî MCP only

- Use **bored MCP tools** for **all** board/column/card reads and writes: `list_boards`, `get_board`, `list_columns`, `list_cards`, `get_card`, **`get_card_by_number`**, `create_card`, **`update_card`**, **`move_card`**, `delete_*`, `reorder_columns`, etc.
- **Do not** call the bored HTTP API with `curl`, scripts, or ad-hoc clients unless MCP is broken or unavailable ‚Äî then say so once, fall back briefly, and still obey **one card**, trunk-based branches, **no stacking branches**.
- **Global (all projects):** Keep **`~/.cursor/mcp.json`** **`mcpServers`** in lockstep with **`~/.claude.json`** ‚Äî copy **wholesale** when Cursor MCP drifts (same **`command` / `args` / `env`** per server). Full playbook: **`mcp-restart-discipline.mdc`** (this repo = **`~/.cursor/rules/`** via dotfiles sync). **`chmod 600`** **`~/.cursor/mcp.json`** when it holds secrets. Do not paste secrets into chat.
- **All projects ‚Äî bored MCP (default; unless you say otherwise):** **`https://bored.desync.link`** + **`bored:prod:access`** unless you instruct otherwise. **`command`** = absolute **`bored-mcp`**. Workspace **`.cursor/mcp.json`** is **gitignored**; **`.cursor/mcp.json.example`** stays empty ‚Äî real config comes from **Claude ‚Üí Cursor sync**, not a committed snippet with secrets. Rebuild **`cargo build -p mcp --release`** when MCP **code** changes. Do not add **`bored-dev`** / duplicate **`bored`** on your own initiative.
